t summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":33,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":42,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Coleclough was born in 1295, in Calverhall, Shropshire, England. She married Sir William De Caverall in 1318, in Prees, Shropshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1370, in Worfield, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1295–1370":"1295–1370","1294–1337":"1294–1337","1320–Female":"1320–Surnud","1322–1368":"1322–1368","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1368":"1368","1322":"1322","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","1295":"1295","1294":"1294","1370":"1370","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Whitchurch, Shropshire, England":"Whitchurch, Shropshire, England","Adderley, Shropshire, England":"Adderley, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hallon, Shropshire, England":"Hallon, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Worfield, Shropshire, England":"Worfield, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Prees, Shropshire, England":"Prees, Shropshire, England","Calverhall, Shropshire, England":"Calverhall, Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"1295–1370":"1295–1370","1294–1337":"1294–1337","1320–Female":"1320–Kuollut","1322